A man has died after a wall collapsed during a demolition exercise in Gardens Cape Town. CAPE TOWN - A man has died after a wall collapsed during a demolition exercise in Gardens Cape Town.The 20-year-old man was among a construction team working on a house on Scott Street.It's understood he had been demolishing a wall when it toppled on top of him on Thursday afternoon.ER24's Russel Meiring says, ER24 paramedics along with Life Healthcare and Ezra services arrived on the scene and on further inspection we discovered that the man had been pulled from the rubble by his colleagues as well as a member of the public. &quot;We assessed the man and found that he has sustained numerous injuries and showed no signs of life. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)